values:
So back at school and back in classes.&nbsp; My classes this year are going to be tough and a LOT of work.&nbsp; Methods is basically pre-service student teaching.&nbsp; I'll be spending three days a week in a classroom in Keene, mostly observing, but teaching a few lessons here and there.&nbsp; What they told us is to put ourselves out there and volunteer to do anything... reading, walking kids to and from lunch, gym etc.&nbsp; Yeah, I plan on kissing as much ass as I can.&nbsp; So that class is two classes... a lecture type thing on campus and field experience.&nbsp; My last class this semester is "Creating social context"&nbsp; which I guess is how social/environmental/developmental issues/stuff effect learning.&nbsp; It should be good.&nbsp; The teacher specalized in sped, so it will be one of the only classes that I have taken that focuses on sped and learning disabilities and stuff.&nbsp; whatever.

also today, I made myself go to the gym today.&nbsp; I went to kickboxing class.&nbsp; I love it!&nbsp; they offer it three days a week and I'm thinking about going those three days, tues, thurs and sun.&nbsp; We'll see.&nbsp;&nbsp;

In other news, living in the suite totally rocks.&nbsp; I get along with all of the girls really well... and... if you've been on facebook recently, there are some pretty hot pictures of me and a few of the girls at the lab n' lager, a really nice bar that has half off drinks for girls on friday or saturday night from like 9 or 10 to 11... so if anyones in the keene area...

&nbsp;So I've called the Mountain View twice now, and I haven't heard back from them yet.&nbsp; Ok, I called them for the second time today at like noon, but still.&nbsp; The first time I called was Friday afternoon and I still haven't heard back.&nbsp; If they dont want me back then they aren't going to get me.&nbsp; I can find a better place to spend my time at and maybe make some more money at.&nbsp; So there Mountain View, suck on that!&nbsp; anyway, the Cabot has a new restaurant and I applied there and it feels good, so hopefully I'll get a call from them to come in for an interview.&nbsp; *cross fingers*&nbsp; I'm also putting apps into applebees and the 99, but with gas being the price that it is, the Cabot would be ideal.&nbsp; I rrrrrreeeeeeeaaaaaallllllyyyyyy hope that the cabot calls me.&nbsp;&nbsp;

anyways, on a more positive note, I bought these really fabulous sandals from Rite-aid today for a little under 8 bucks.&nbsp; Ok, so they're not that fabulous.&nbsp; But they're black and more dressy than the crappy dirty old navy sandals that I've been running around in for, well, ever.

also diet/exercise has been lax.&nbsp; I ran yesterday, monday, and it was pathetic.&nbsp; I couldn't even make it Powder Hill.&nbsp; The last time I was home and went running, I easily made it to Blackberry Lane, which is about a half mile from my house.&nbsp; I didn't run today, but tomorrow I"m going to the dump and back.&nbsp; Maybe running on flats will be easier than uphill!

So, sifting through some of my school notes (mostly children's lit notes) and after watching the little mermaid, this question&nbsp;jumped into my head, and now&nbsp;I'm stumped.

How do mermaids (ok,&nbsp;being more PC... merpeople) reproduce?&nbsp;&nbsp;Like people?&nbsp; Or like fish,&nbsp;in one of&nbsp;the&nbsp;ways fish reproduce?

It hasn't bothered&nbsp;me enough to like google it or something, but its still strange.&nbsp; People tops and fishy bottoms.&nbsp;&nbsp;Is the internal organs set up the same, human on the top half and fish on the bottom?&nbsp; Hmmm... something to ponder.&nbsp;

&nbsp;well, three finals down, one to go.&nbsp; I'm trying to bang out a 6-8 page paper on animal assisted therapy, focusing on sexually abused children and old people.&nbsp; yeah, its as fun as it sounds.&nbsp; but its only 9:30, and I have until 1pm to get it done, assuming I can focus.&nbsp; but my mind isn't focusing.&nbsp; I just took a 100 question multiple choice test on social psychology, dealing mostly with cognitive dissonance (which I find myself in a state of), so I basically want to throw my self out of my first floor window... and land approximately three feet down on the grass, where there is a crazy squirrel.&nbsp; Bah humbug!
&nbsp;
oh, and last night (dont even ask how&nbsp;I came to this thought, probably because I took a study break to watch rent on fx) anyway... I started wondering what my life would be like if it was... a musical!&nbsp; Seriously.&nbsp; then the only thing I could think of was Family Guy when Peter has his own theme music (I made myself giggle) and then I was trying to think of plays or whatever that it might be like and I came up with nothing.&nbsp; Well, high school musical came to mind, but I can't play basketball very well and I'm not a mathalete... so that went out the door.&nbsp; yeah, need to start working on that paper...

&nbsp;I was just wondering what happened to the world today.&nbsp; Maybe spring fever, but probably not with this fun little snow storm that we're getting now.&nbsp; Ok, maybe not snow storm, but its snowing...

Anywhoo... the reason for questioning the rotation of the earth is that Tom had a girl over.&nbsp; and it wasn't Lindsey.&nbsp; *I can hear the gasps of surprise*&nbsp; He's been pining over her for so long that it was really surprising to see him walk in the door with someone other than Lindsey.&nbsp; So they were in the family room for a while watching Across the Universe (cause I could hear it all the way downstairs).&nbsp; So about 9pm, when Cassie gets home from sports awards, she comes barrelling down the front stairs and looks at me and at the top of her whisper says "They're making out!"&nbsp; And I"m pretty sure Cassie wouldn't lie.&nbsp; And I think her name is Elaine Frenette, and I"m pretty sure she has a little sister around cassie's age named Leah, which doesn't help me much.&nbsp;&nbsp;

So yes, something happened today and it was quite monumental.&nbsp; I'm still not sure what to make of it.&nbsp; I dont think any of us will get any information from Tom... he's in that "Im the most important person in the world" selfish stage of his life right now.&nbsp; but maybe *cross fingers* now that he's finally 100% over Lindsey, he'll turn back to normal.
